Excerpt from _src/main/org/codehaus/groovy/runtime/DefaultGroovyMethods.java_

```
/**
 * Logical conjunction of two boolean operators.
 *
 * @param left left operator
 * @param right right operator
 * @return result of logical conjunction
 * @since 1.0
 */
public static Boolean and(Boolean left, Boolean right) {
	if (right == null) {
		right = Boolean.FALSE;
	}
	return left && right;
}
```

My point is that the Groovydoc for both arguments is identical, but the right-argument now explicitly adheres to the Groovy truth-convention, the documentation doesn't reflect that.

